If you only have one set of pots and pans in your kitchen, this should be it. I’ve tried just about every set of cookware on the planet  and not only is Hestan beautiful to look at the NanoBond technology is a game  changer.  It is unlike anything else I have ever used. It creates a nonstick surface without having a black coating that eventually, inevitably, scratches off. Typically I try to stay away from sets because they always include a piece or two I might not use, but this one is perfectly curated with every size I actually use. Miller & Lux is thrilled to announce our next wine masterclass in partnership with Larkmead on Wednesday, March 29th at 6pm. The broad patch of Calistoga that Larkmead Vineyards calls home has been under vine since the mid-1800s and has witnessed the turning of two centuries. Napa Valley has transformed from a vinous vestige of the Wild West to one of the most preeminent wine regions of the world. Larkmead has played an active role in that swell, as their grapes have contributed to countless, celebrated Napa Valley wines across the decades. Guided by Avery Heelan, winemaker of Larkmead. The Larkmead wines showcased have been thoughtfully paired alongside a 4-course menu.
 
Go to millerandluxrestaurant.com and hit the upcoming events page for more details or email events@millerandluxrestaurant.com for reservations.

Gentlemen… as we pull ourselves out of the long, dark days of winter, it’s time to start thinking about our skin again. I just got a lovely friends and family gift from Le Domaine @beau.domaine skin care from Miraval, in the lush Rhône Valley wine region of Provence, France. I opened it up in my kitchen this morning and the packaging alone is stunning. Based on 20 years of anti-aging science studying the phenolic compounds of grapes and grapevines, each formula of Le Domaine is perfected like a Grand Cru, resulting in highly effective skin care where every detail serves a purpose. Made from upcycled grape pomace recovered after making wine with Grenache seeds, Syrah seeds and skins associated with Resveratrol (grapevine tendrils) and the addition of Apigenin (chamomile), and Catechin (green tea) Le Domaine is designed to delay oxidation at the cellular level. It’s skincare you can feel and see a difference from the first application, plus It smells amazing. Get your skin in shape, summer is around the corner. I love this stuff. Thank you @beau.domaine

Come see us at Miller & Lux! Here’s a bit of our backstory:
With deep rooted history in the American West, Miller & Lux is the story of two passionate immigrants. Starting with a butcher shop in the 1850’s, founders Henry Miller and Charles Lux grew the business into one of the largest cattle ranchers in America, gaining the title as “The Cattle Kings of California”. Today, their legacy is well represented in a relaxed luxury setting that celebrates the good life.

I moved to San Francisco in 2007 because this city, one where some of the best restaurants in the world have shaped the way people think about and enjoy food, was where I wanted to open my flagship restaurant, Wayfare Tavern. It was the people who came, brought energy and an appreciation for what I was doing there – blending my southern roots with California Cuisine – that made Wayfare a success, and allowed me to open Miller & Lux, an American steakhouse and truly the restaurant of my dreams. And we’re just getting started. We recently put our love into Union Square with Miller & Lux Provisions, our two café projects, and are taking over the landmark Town Hall restaurant this winter. I knew it then and I know it now – I couldn’t have picked a better city for my growing restaurant group. It all starts here, and the best is yet to come. #ItAllStartsHereSF #ad @itallstartsheresf
Royal Myiagi Oysters with Whipped Apple Cider Mignonette and Shiso. @millerandlux

Setting up @millerandluxprovisions for success took careful planning and consideration with our culinary team. It was our first grab and go concept and we wanted to get it right. One thing was for sure, Our friends at @turbocheftech made it easy, from one side of the park to the other. Our amazing breakfast sandwiches and warm flaky croissants at the patisserie and our juicy and crispy chicken at the rotisserie are all perfect every time. If you are planning a QSR+ restaurant experience, I can’t recommend @turbocheftech highly enough. Their engineers came out and we developed custom cook times with custom settings on the machines so our team can hit a button, focus on customer service and let turbo chef take care of the food. I’m beyond impressed. I’m putting Turbo Chefs everywhere.
